Great American Coffee Taste Test

Author

Linus Lach

Packages

The following packages are used throughout the article

library(tidyverse)
library(haven)
library(janitor)
library(gtExtras)
library(stringr)

Initial data manipulation

Reading the data.

data <- read.csv("GACTT_RESULTS_ANONYMIZED_v2.csv")

Replacing empty characters with NA values.

data_conv_na <- data %>%
  mutate_if(is_character,zap_empty) %>%
  clean_names()

Preselection of potentially interesting variables

Variables listed in the select function seem to be somewhat relevant heuristically. Further analysis could be conducted to check if the deselected features have been wrongfully removed.

data_select_aggregated <- data_conv_na %>%

It seems like some of the columns include seemingly redundant information, e.g. a person who specified to only drink black coffee does not add anything else to the beverage.

data_add_to_coffee <- data_select_aggregated %>%
  select(do_you_usually_add_anything_to_your_coffee,
         what_kind_of_sugar_or_sweetener_do_you_add,
         what_kind_of_dairy_do_you_add,
         what_else_do_you_add_to_your_coffee)

Additionally, most information regarding the complementary ingredients can be found in the do_you_usually_add_anything_to_your_coffee variable which motivates the elimination of the following variables. Furthermore, replace NA values in nominal features with "unknown". This might become problematic later when modeling correlations, so caution is advised.

data_select_aggregated <- data_select_aggregated %>%
  select(-c(do_you_usually_add_anything_to_your_coffee,
            how_else_do_you_brew_coffee_at_home,
            what_kind_of_sugar_or_sweetener_do_you_add,
            what_kind_of_dairy_do_you_add,
            what_else_do_you_add_to_your_coffee,
            please_specify_what_your_favorite_coffee_drink_is,
            on_the_go_where_do_you_typically_purchase_coffee
                                     )) %>%
  mutate(across(where(is_character), ~replace_na(.,"unkown")))
